About the job
Job Title: Junior Software Engineer
 Company: Winfra
 Location: Remote
 Experience: 0–2 Years (Freshers Encouraged)
 Employment Type: Full-time
About the Role

Are you a passionate coder eager to launch your career in tech? At Winfra, we’re looking for motivated Junior Software Engineers—whether you're a recent graduate or have up to 2 years of experience.
If you're excited about learning, building, and working on impactful projects, we’d love to hear from you. Comprehensive training will be provided to set you up for success.
 
 
What You’ll Do

Support the development, testing, and maintenance of web and mobile applications
Collaborate with senior developers on new feature development
Write clean, efficient, and scalable code
Participate in code reviews and team discussions
Debug and upgrade existing software
Stay current with the latest technologies and development practices


 What We’re Looking For

A Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, IT, or related field (final-year students may also apply)
Basic understanding of programming languages like Java, Python, PHP, or JavaScript
Familiarity with databases like MySQL or MongoDB is a plus
Strong problem-solving and analytical abilities
Willingness to learn and grow within a collaborative team
Good communication and interpersonal skills

Location: Remote (Pan-India)
Type: Freelance / Part-time / Hourly
Pay: Up to ₹2300/ Hour (Paid Weekly)
Experience Level: Freshers to Experts
Start Date: Immediate
No. of Openings: 100+


🚀 About the Opportunity

Are you passionate about frontend development, coding, teaching, or AI? We're hiring skilled coders & frontend developers to train AI models how to write better code and build stunning websites. No contracts. No meetings. Just meaningful, well-paid freelance work you can do from anywhere in India.


💻 What You’ll Do?

Solve real-world frontend coding problems in HTML, CSS, JS, React, and more
Review & improve AI-generated code – point out bugs, UI/UX issues, and offer suggestions
Help AI models learn what beautiful, functional, and accessible design looks like
Provide expert insights on web design patterns, usability, and accessibility
Share your developer brain to make future AI more intelligent


✅ Who Can Apply?

Solid knowledge of JavaScript, HTML/CSS, and modern frameworks (React, Next.js, Vue, etc.)
Freshers, college students, freelancers, or professionals — all welcome
Degree is NOT required (but practical skills are a must)
